"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The issue with the code is in the lines 28-30 where the roc_curve function is called. The roc_curve function expects the second argument to be an array of probabilities of the positive class, but y_score is a 2D array where each row is an array of probabilities of all classes for a sample. The second issue is with the line 29 where the fpr and tpr lists are indexed with 'i' but these lists are not initialized with enough elements, which will cause an IndexError.\",\n  \"patch\": \"28,31c28,31\\n<for i in range(n_classes):\\n---\\n>for i in range(n_classes):\\n>    fpr_class, tpr_class, thresh = roc_curve(y_onehot_test[:, i], y_score[:, i])\\n>    roc_auc.append(auc(fpr_class, tpr_class))\\n>    fpr.append(fpr_class)\\n>    tpr.append(tpr_class)\\n\"\n}"